rlEmbWeb.name: rlEmbWeb
rlEmbWeb.contactinfo: Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose , CA 95134-1706 USA Website: Cisco Small Business Home http://www.cisco.com/smb>;, Cisco Small Business Support Community <http://www.cisco.com/go/smallbizsupport>
rlEmbWeb.description: This private MIB module adds MIBs to EMBWEB (Embedded Web Server).

rlEmWebMibVersion.name: rlEmWebMibVersion
rlEmWebMibVersion.description: Embedded web version, the current version is 2.

rlEmWebWebSite.name: rlEmWebWebSite
rlEmWebWebSite.description: Link for the vendor web site used to retrive information.

rlEmWebSecurityTable.name: rlEmWebSecurityTable
rlEmWebSecurityTable.description: Security Table whose entry is composed of username and Password, group and access privileges for each user. The access privileges can be one or more of none, read-files, read-write, and super.

rlEmWebSecurityEntry.name: rlEmWebSecurityEntry
rlEmWebSecurityEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlEmWebSecurityIpAddr.name: rlEmWebSecurityIpAddr
rlEmWebSecurityIpAddr.description: IP Address to send the traps to.0 means doesn't want to receive traps.

rlEmWebSecurityPort.name: rlEmWebSecurityPort
rlEmWebSecurityPort.description: Port to send the traps to.

rlEmWebSecuritySnmpVersion.name: rlEmWebSecuritySnmpVersion
rlEmWebSecuritySnmpVersion.description: SNMP version supported by this user. For the agent use.

rlEmWebSecurityStatus.name: rlEmWebSecurityStatus
rlEmWebSecurityStatus.description: The status of the security table entry. It's used to delete an entry

rlEmWebCloseTimeout.name: rlEmWebCloseTimeout
rlEmWebCloseTimeout.description: This variable defines the maximum time period in seconds that a TCP connection can stay open without depending on the TCP timeout mechanism

rlEmWebReceiveTimeout.name: rlEmWebReceiveTimeout
rlEmWebReceiveTimeout.description: This variable defines the maximum time period in seconds that a TCP connection can wait for data which hasn't arrived

rlEmWebMaxIdleTimeout.name: rlEmWebMaxIdleTimeout
rlEmWebMaxIdleTimeout.description: This variable defines the maximum HTTP Idle time period in seconds for a TCP connection.If another request isn't made at this period, the connection is closed. The value 0 is supported as 'no timeout'.

rlEmWebSetEWSfilesStatus.name: rlEmWebSetEWSfilesStatus
rlEmWebSetEWSfilesStatus.description: This variable sets the status of the embedded Web Server files to either closed or opened.

rlEmbeddedWebApplied.name: rlEmbeddedWebApplied
rlEmbeddedWebApplied.description: Specifies if the device supports Embedded WEB: true - suppotrs false - does not support

rlEmWebHttpPort.name: rlEmWebHttpPort
rlEmWebHttpPort.description: Specifies the TCP port the embedded web uses for HTTP sessions.

rlEmWebHttpsPort.name: rlEmWebHttpsPort
rlEmWebHttpsPort.description: Specifies the TCP port the embedded web uses for HTTPS sessions.

rlEmWebCertificateCountryName.name: rlEmWebCertificateCountryName
rlEmWebCertificateCountryName.description: Value of country name field that will appear when a new certificate is generated.

rlEmWebCertificateStateOrProvinceName.name: rlEmWebCertificateStateOrProvinceName
rlEmWebCertificateStateOrProvinceName.description: Value of state or province name field that will appear when a new certificate is generated.

rlEmWebCertificateLocalityName.name: rlEmWebCertificateLocalityName
rlEmWebCertificateLocalityName.description: Value of locality field that will appear when a new certificate is generated.

rlEmWebCertificateOrganizationName.name: rlEmWebCertificateOrganizationName
rlEmWebCertificateOrganizationName.description: Value of organization field that will appear when a new certificate is generated.

rlEmWebCertificateCommonName.name: rlEmWebCertificateCommonName
rlEmWebCertificateCommonName.description: Value of common name field that will appear when a new certificate is generated.

rlEmWebCertificateRegenerate.name: rlEmWebCertificateRegenerate
rlEmWebCertificateRegenerate.description: Setting to a regenerateCertificate causes a new certifiacte to be generated and to be used for all new sessions.

rlEmWebRsaKeyLength.name: rlEmWebRsaKeyLength
rlEmWebRsaKeyLength.description: Setting the RSA key size that will be created when rlEmWebRegenerateCertificateAndKey will be set to regenerateCertificateAndKey.

rlEmWebDebug.name: rlEmWebDebug
rlEmWebDebug.description: MIB variable for setting debug information.

rlEmWebURL.name: rlEmWebURL
rlEmWebURL.description: The URL through which the EWS of this device can be accessed.

rlEmWebDisplayNonPresentEntities.name: rlEmWebDisplayNonPresentEntities
rlEmWebDisplayNonPresentEntities.description: This object indicates whether the EWS is required to display non-present entities (like non-present ports, IP addresses on non-present ports etc.) on it's screens.

rlEmWebCertificateExists.name: rlEmWebCertificateExists
rlEmWebCertificateExists.description: This object indicates whether a certificate has been generated.

rlEmWebHttpsActiveCertificateId.name: rlEmWebHttpsActiveCertificateId
rlEmWebHttpsActiveCertificateId.description: By setting this scalar https is notified that the certificate and key with this index should be used for new https sessions. Even if the certifcate or key doesn't exist yet the operation will succeed.

rlEmWebExtraPort.name: rlEmWebExtraPort
rlEmWebExtraPort.description: Specifies the TCP port the embedded web uses for The Extra Port sessions.

rlEmWebExtraPortType.name: rlEmWebExtraPortType
rlEmWebExtraPortType.description: Specifies the Extra Port Type HTTP/HTTPS for all sessions.

rlEmWebMaxHttpsIdleTimeout.name: rlEmWebMaxHttpsIdleTimeout
rlEmWebMaxHttpsIdleTimeout.description: This variable defines the maximum HTTPS Idle time period in seconds for a web connection.If another request isn't made at this period, the connection is closed. The value 0 is supported as 'no timeout'.

rlEmWebServiceEntry.name: rlEmWebServiceEntry
rlEmWebServiceEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlEmWebServiceEnable.name: rlEmWebServiceEnable
rlEmWebServiceEnable.description: Indicates whether the service is enabled or not. if set to 'default' will the service to go back to its initialization default status.

rlEmWebServicePort.name: rlEmWebServicePort
rlEmWebServicePort.description: Indicates whether the TCP port on which service is listening. value 0 will set the service to it's default port

rlEmWebServiceMaxUsers.name: rlEmWebServiceMaxUsers
rlEmWebServiceMaxUsers.description: The maximal number of users for this service.

rlEmWebServiceProtocol.name: rlEmWebServiceProtocol
rlEmWebServiceProtocol.description: Indicates the protocol that the service operates on. Note that the general HTTP service can have only the http value and the general HTTPS service can have only the https value. setting the field to 'default' will cause the service to go back to it's initialization settings.

rlEmWebServiceCertificateId.name: rlEmWebServiceCertificateId
rlEmWebServiceCertificateId.description: Indicates the certificate used by the service if rlEmWebServiceProtocol is https. A value of 0 indicates that a certificate has not been assigned to this service. setting this field to 1000 will cause the service to go back to it's initialization value.

rlEmWebServiceMaxIdleTimeOut.name: rlEmWebServiceMaxIdleTimeOut
rlEmWebServiceMaxIdleTimeOut.description: This variable defines the maximum Idle time period in seconds for a TCP connection. If another request isn't made at this period, the connection is closed. The value 0 is supported as 'no timeout'.setting this field to 3932160 will cause the service to go back to it's initialization value.
